  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "The test was failing because it was checking for context.Canceled using xerrors.Is, but postgres returns a different error (\"pq: canceling statement due to user request\") when a query is cancelled. This change uses database.IsQueryCanceledError which properly handles both context.Canceled and postgres-specific cancellation errors.\r\n\r\nfixes https://github.com/coder/internal/issues/702",
